<body>
<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Use a Communications Degree</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1003" relname="span">Communications degrees can be used in many ways</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="2" relname="purpose">to obtain work in a variety of areas .</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="joint">The field of communications is broad</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1005" relname="span">and you can " tailor " your degree to something</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="5" relname="elaboration">that truly fits your interests .</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1008" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1009" relname="preparation">Training in communications</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1010" relname="span">Find a college</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="9" relname="elaboration">that best suits you .</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1012" relname="contrast">Many colleges offer degrees in communications ,</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="contrast">but some programs are considered to be better than others .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1014" relname="span">Consider many different things</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1016" relname="span">when seeking out a college</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="14" relname="elaboration">that offers communications degrees ,</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1015" relname="span">such as the location of the school , the price of the schooling , and how prestigious the program is considered to be .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">Bear in mind</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1019" relname="same_unit">that</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1021" relname="condition">just because a school offers communications ,</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="span">this does not mean</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="20" relname="elaboration">that it is a strong program .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1022" relname="span">Select a specialization .</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="24" relname="condition">When you seek a degree in communications ,</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1024" relname="span">you must often choose an area of or focus .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1025" relname="joint">Many colleges offer different areas of specialization , such as journalism , advertising , or public relations .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1028" relname="background">Often you wo n't have to decide your focus in your first year or two of college or even your major ,</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">so take this time</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1029" relname="span">to explore the different areas</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1030" relname="span">by taking classes</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="29" relname="elaboration">that relate to your own communications interests .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1034" relname="span">You can always talk to your advisor about the classes</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="elaboration">you can take ,</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1034" relname="purpose">to help you make your decision .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1033" relname="elaboration">Get involved .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1035" relname="joint">Many colleges have communication related clubs , such as an advertising club or the school newspaper .</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1037" relname="span">Not only are these great ways</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="36" relname="purpose">to get involved</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1039" relname="preparation">and meet new people ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1040" relname="span">they are often a great way</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="39" relname="purpose">to get real world experience and maybe even some extra money .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1042" relname="span">However , some of these things can add to your workload ,</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="41" relname="purpose">so do n't let it take precedence over your studies .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1043" relname="sequence">Getting employed in the communications field</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1044" relname="sequence">Put your qualifications to good use .</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="span">Colleges are often able to help you get internships</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="45" relname="purpose">to get you on your way .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="span">This is a great place</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1049" relname="span">to start ,</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1051" relname="span">as internships are a good way</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="49" relname="purpose">to get more real world experience</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1050" relname="sequence">and get your name out there .</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1052" relname="sequence">Sometimes , internships can lead to job offers .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1054" relname="span">Start looking for job openings online in a field</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="53" relname="elaboration">you desire .</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1056" relname="span">Use your degree</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="span">to show employers</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="56" relname="elaboration">that you know your field inside out .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1059" relname="span">Use your prior college work experience</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="60" relname="attribution">to show</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="span">that you know how to work in your field .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1061" relname="joint">Do n't give up ,</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="63" relname="attribution">and remember</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="span">you may not make a million dollars overnight ,</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1062" relname="contrast">but hard work pays off !</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1065" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1066" relname="joint">Always work hard</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="span">and do n't get down on yourself</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="67" relname="condition">if you do n't find work right away .</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1068" relname="span">Always have a " learning attitude "</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="span">you can learn a lot about communicating</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1071" relname="contrast">simply by watching TV</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1071" relname="contrast">or talking to people in everyday situations .</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1072" relname="joint">Have good grammar .</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1074" relname="span">It is unhelpful to read work</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1075" relname="span">written by students and workers in the communications field</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1076" relname="span">that shows a lack of good grammar and spelling ,</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1077" relname="span">which is the foundation of the very tool</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="77" relname="elaboration">that they have chosen to work with , language .</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="80" relname="condition">If you are weak in this area ,</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1078" relname="span">do something about it .</segment>
